  "text": "Data from the present study and from [CITATION_1] have been used to augment a phylogenetic tree composed of 77 biallelic polymorphisms ( fig. 1 ). Thirtyseven binary haplotypes were found in the total sample of 608 African subjects. The notation of [CITATION_2] for these haplotypes was kept, except for four haplotypes that are described here for the first time. These are: (1) haplotype 12b, carrying the M218 mutation but ancestral at M109; (2) haplotype 19b, carrying the derived alleles at M236 and M288 but ancestral at M146; (3) haplotype 41b, carrying the mutated allele at M98 but ancestral at M85; and (4) haplotype 117b, carrying the M269 derived allele on a M207/ M173 background.",
